    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prints on photographic materials achieved by controlled exposure to white, red, green, or blue light and processed chemically. Distinguished from 'electrophotographic laser prints' that create images via a beam of light to etch onto a photoconductive drum from which images are transferred by electrostatic copying to paper.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051051/Jürgens, The Digital Print (2009)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Afdrukken op fotografische materialen door gecontroleerde blootstelling aan wit, rood, groen of blauw licht en chemische bewerking. Te onderscheiden van elektrofotografische laserprints, waarbij afbeeldingen met een lichtstraal op een fotogeleidende trommel worden geprojecteerd en vervolgens elektrostatisch worden overgezet op papier.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>控制感光材料於白、紅、綠或藍光的曝光，並經化學處理所完成之印刷。與「電照相雷射印刷」的差異在於，後者經由光束在光電導滾筒上蝕刻來創造圖像，再藉靜電複製，把圖像從光電導滾筒傳輸到紙上。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
